"collapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"exp=
and-control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Exp=
and source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">HTTP/1.1 200 Ok
Content-Type: application/json
=20
{
    "data": {
        "customers": [
        {
            "customerId": {
                "id" : "12345",
                "idScheme": "CustomerInternalId"
            },
            "firstName": "Samuel",
            "lastName": "Johnson",
            "middleName": "Andrew",
            "dateOfBirth": "1998-07-03",
            "gender": {
                "code": "M"
            },
            "status": {
                "code": "A"
            }
        },
        ...
        {
            "customerId": {
                "id" : "67890",
                "idScheme": "CustomerInternalId"
            },
            "firstName": "Samantha",
            "lastName": "Jones",
            "middleName": Louisa,
            "dateOfBirth": "1985-10-23",
            "gender": {
                "code": "F"
            },
            "status": {
                "code": "A"
            }
        }
        ]
    }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"APIDesignGuidelines-PUT">PUT</h3>
<p>PUT is to be used for creating or updating the state of the resource bei=
ng called. It should be possible to make the same call against a resource u=
sing a PUT and the outcome on resource state to be the same (idempotent), a=
ssuming no other agent impacts the resource between calls.</p>
<p>The use of PUT for update operations creates some complexity. PUT is mea=
nt to replace the <em>entire</em> resource with a new representation, howev=
er many organisations use PUT for partial updates by only passing in the re=
source attributes to change. This approach however would not guarantee idem=
potency (repeatability) and we do not support this approach on Westpac Mesh=
 - PUT must be used to replace the <em>entire</em> resource.</p>
<p>The approaches available to support <em>partial</em> updates, listed in =
order of most preferred to least preferred are:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use PATCH to update the subset of fields required.&nbsp; Note that you =
cannot use PATCH to insert or delete items within a nested collection conta=
ined inside the resource; you will need to use POST AND DELETE respectively=
 on a sub-resource.</li>
<li>Use POST on the primary resource and append '/do/<em>verb</em>' to the =
URI.&nbsp; eg. POST /customers/33245/do/terminate.&nbsp; This approach is a=
ppropriate to encapsulate a discrete action to be applied against the resou=
rce, equivalent to creating a new HTTP verb to describe the action.&nbsp; H=
owever, it is not appropriate to use&nbsp;<em>'/do/update'</em>&nbsp;to sup=
port partial resource updates as PATCH should be used for this purpose.</li=
>
<li>Use PUT on a sub-resource of the primary resource which represents the =
collection of fields to be updated - all fields of the sub-resource MUST be=
 supplied. &nbsp;However, we don't want to end up with a design where every=
 field becomes its own sub-resource. &nbsp;Where the sub-resource contains =
a collection of fields it needs to be named in an intuitive fashion.&nbsp; =
Note: each attribute or property of the resource can only be present in ONE=
 sub-resource.</li>
<li>Use POST to a new resource, which is used only for updates, that is nam=
ed similarly to the primary resource. eg. POST /customerUpdates.&nbsp; This=
 option is suitable where the unique identifier for the resource to be upda=
ted cannot be described via the URI.&nbsp; This could occur where the provi=
der system (or API) does not expose the unique identifier or the resource c=
ontains a nested collection and there is a desire to insert, update or dele=
te item(s) in the collection along with scalar attributes of the resource w=
ithin a single endpoint.</li>
<li>Use DELETE to remove the resource, then use POST to (re)create the reso=
urce.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Note</strong>.&nbsp; It is permissible to apply PUT to a collect=
ion resource but note that it is expected that you will replace ALL items w=
ithin that collection.&nbsp; If you want to selectively update items within=
 the collection use PATCH instead.</p>
<p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
<p>PUT&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://www.example.com/buckets/secret_stuff" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">/</a>customers/12345</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">PUT request: single resource</b><span class=3D"coll=
apse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-c=
ontrol-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand s=
ource</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">PUT /customers/12345 HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
=20
{
    "firstName": "Samuel",
    "lastName": "Johnson",
    "middleName": null,
    "dateOfBirth": "1998-07-03",
    "gender": {
        "code": "M"
    },
    "status": {
        "code": "A"
   }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">PUT response: single resource</b><span class=3D"col=
lapse-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-=
control-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand =
source</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: js; gutter: false; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Confl=
uence">HTTP/1.1 204 No Content
Content-Type: application/json</pre>
</div>
</div>
